                                                                                                                                  Business Briefs

               
	 Mumbai, Jan. 14: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) today announced that it has made another gas discovery in the Krishna-Godavari basin. In a late evening announcement, the company said the discovery was made in the exploratory block KG-OSN-2001/1 (KG-III-5), located in Krishna offshore basin on the east coast of the country. This is the third gas discovery in this block.
              
	 Hyderabad, Jan. 14: Union petroleum minister Murli Deora today said a decision on the fuel price hike will be taken at the group of ministers meeting on January 17. 
              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 14: Power Grid Corporation has floated a joint venture agreement with IL amp;FS to develop intra-state and sub-transmission projects for domestic and global power utilities.
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 14: The dispute between industrialist Rahul Bajaj and his younger brother Shishir over the division of the family business appears set to drag further with both sides hinting at the improbability of an out-of-court settlement anytime soon.
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 14: India will begin construction on strategic crude oil storages this year as insurance against disruptions during emergencies. Hindustan Construction has emerged as the lowest bidder.
                                                            
